{
  "texts": [
    "Chen et al (2023) utilize a Gaussian mixture prior and nonlinear structural equations to model topic dependencies between hierarchical levels.",
    "The main issue of the parametric setting is that topic hierarchies cannot grow dynamically since their width and height must be predetermined before training.",
    "Researchers apply NTMs to discover topics from short texts.",
    "Short texts, prevalent on the Internet in various forms such as tweets, comments, and news headlines, serve as a common medium for individuals to express ideas, comments, and opinions.",
    "However, normal topic models often struggle to effectively handle short texts."
  ]
}